        "title": "What Happens During a Routine Dental Check Up?",
        "excerpt": "Most would agree that routine dental check ups are an integral and important part of overall dental health and wellness. That said understanding what happens during a routine dental checkup is important. Keep in mind that regular dental exams should occur about every six months or twice a year. Obviously, the first part of any [&hellip;]",
        "author": "Top Pinole Dental",
        "content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Most would agree that routine dental check ups are an integral and important part of overall dental health and wellness. That said understanding what happens during a routine dental checkup is important. Keep in mind that regular dental exams should occur about every six months or twice a year. Obviously, the first part of any dental checkup is reporting in with the receptionist of your dental care provider\u2019s office. Friendly staff are there to greet you and make you feel at ease leading into your routine check.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"left\",\"id\":1280,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"alignleft size-large\"><img src=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/routine-dental-checkup.jpg\" alt=\"Preparation for the actual dentist portion of the visit\" class=\"wp-image-1280\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n<!-- \/wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Preparation for The Actual Dentist Portion of the Visit<\/h5>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Usually the next person that you will come into contact with is your dental hygienist or dental assistant. It is important to note that dental hygienists are trained dental professionals that are experienced in administering routine dental care. This includes everything from cleanings to simple dental procedures in preparation for the actual dentist portion of the visit. Never underestimate the importance of the dental hygienist or dental assistant as they play a vital role in overall dental healthcare and wellness. The next thing that typically happens is that your dentist will check your dental related history.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"right\",\"id\":1282,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"alignright size-large\"><img src=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/dental-routing-checkup.jpg\" alt=\"Plaque and tartar that may collect below the gum line\" class=\"wp-image-1282\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n<!-- \/wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Plaque and Tartar That May Collect Below the Gum Line<\/h5>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Everything from current medications to arthritic conditions and diabetes as well as pregnancy is considered prior to any dental work being accomplished. While this is happening, you may actually be having your teeth cleaned by the hygienist. The cleaning process involves scraping plaque and tartar that may collect below the gum line as well as above on teeth. The hygienist will then floss between your teeth and remove any food particles. The teeth cleaning process also involves polishing to give teeth a healthy shine. Finally, the dentist will examine your teeth and take x-rays as necessary to determine overall health. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/contact\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Contact<\/a> your Pinole dentists, Dr. Azadeh Hosseini and Dr. Ghazal Hosseini at <a href=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Top Pinole Dental<\/a>, today to learn more about your next routine dental check up.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":6} -->\n<h6>References:<br>[1] <a href=\"https:\/\/www.happykidsdental.org\/dental-health-care-and-coronavirus-considerations\/\">Dental Health Care and Coronavirus Considerations<\/a><br>[2] <a href=\"https:\/\/www.walnutcreekdental.net\/when-do-you-need-teeth-deep-cleaning\/\">When Do You Need Teeth Deep Cleaning?<\/a><\/h6>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->",
