        "title": "Dental Cleaning for Kids: What Is the Best Age to Age Start Regular Cleanings?",
        "excerpt": "The short answer is that dental cleaning for kids can take place as early as when a full set of baby teeth has arrived. That said it is a good idea to begin visiting your pediatric dentist as early as when the child is six months of age. In general, the first cleaning will ideally [&hellip;]",
        "author": "Top Pinole Dental",
        "content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The short answer is that dental cleaning for kids can take place as early as when a full set of baby teeth has arrived. That said it is a good idea to begin visiting your pediatric dentist as early as when the child is six months of age. In general, the first cleaning will ideally occur sometime during the toddler years. This would be around from one year to three years of age. It is recommended that parents prepare their children properly for their first dental visit. Talk with your children to dispel any anxiety and let them know the importance of good dental health. <\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"left\",\"id\":1247,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"alignleft size-large\"><img src=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/Kids-Dental-Cleaning.png\" alt=\"Healthy Teeth Through All Stages of Childhood\" class=\"wp-image-1247\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n<!-- \/wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Healthy Teeth Through All Stages of Childhood<\/h5>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At the end of the day, it is up to parents to make sure that their children learn proper dental care at home. This combined with regular dental visits will greatly increase the likelihood that children will have healthy teeth through all stages of childhood and into adulthood. Regular routine dental visits and regular cleanings along with an effective home dental care regimen is always the best strategy. This combined with proper diet and eating healthy foods that are not damaging to the teeth can go a long way in keeping children\u2019s teeth looking great.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Keep Children Engage in Proper Dental Care While at Home <\/h5>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"right\",\"id\":1246,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"alignright size-large\"><img src=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/Dental-Cleaning-Kids.png\" alt=\"Keep Children Engage in Proper Dental Care While at Home \" class=\"wp-image-1246\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n<!-- \/wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Finally, parents with young children involved in sports should exercise extreme caution and make sure that they wear guards so that their teeth are not injured during sporting activities. This is worth discussing because some children begin sporting events at a very early age. At the end of the day making dental care fun and interesting will keep children engaged in proper dental practices while at home. Talk with your dental care provider to learn more about dental cleaning for children and how it can help encourage good oral hygiene. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/contact\/\">Contact<\/a> your dentist for kids in Pinole, Dr. Azadeh Hosseini and\/or Dr. Ghazal Hosseini at <a href=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/\">Top Pinole Dental<\/a>, today for more information about dental cleaning for kids.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":6} -->\n<h6>References:<br>[1] <a href=\"https:\/\/www.happykidsdental.org\/pediatric-dentistry-for-kids\/\">Pediatric Dentistry for Kids<\/a><br>[2] <a href=\"https:\/\/www.happykidsdental.org\/a-dentist-for-kids-pediatric-dentist-vs-general-dentist\/\">Dental Care For Kids: Pediatric Dentist vs. General Dentist<\/a><\/h6>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
