        "title": "Children\u2019s Adolescents Pediatric Dentistry",
        "excerpt": "Pediatric dentistry is sometimes referred to as pedodontia and offers a wide range of treatment from a dental perspective for children of all ages. This type of dentistry involves treating children of all ages including teenagers and adolescents. Keep in mind that adolescents pediatric dentistry will undergo additional training in order to develop all the [&hellip;]",
        "author": "Top Pinole Dental",
        "content": "<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"right\",\"id\":1178,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"alignright size-large\"><img src=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/06\/Pediatric-Dentist.jpg\" alt=\"Adolescents Pediatric Dentistry\" class=\"wp-image-1178\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n<!-- \/wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Pediatric dentistry is sometimes referred to as pedodontia and offers a wide range of treatment from a dental perspective for children of all ages. This type of dentistry involves treating children of all ages including teenagers and adolescents. Keep in mind that adolescents pediatric dentistry will undergo additional training in order to develop all the skills and knowledge necessary to handle the unique demands of dental care for children. This is important because children require specialized care as their teeth are different from adult\u2019s teeth. The diagnosis and treatment of a wide range of dental issues is what a pediatric dentist does on a daily basis.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Prone to Tooth Decay<\/h5>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>From the eruption of permanent teeth to dealing with gum disease and cavities, this is an important time in a child\u2019s life where close attention to detail in terms of dental health is so important. It is key to note that children are typically more prone to tooth decay and gum disease than adults. This may be because children do not have the discipline to maintain routine home dental care and because of their diet. Preventive dentistry is one of the most important aspects of oral health for children. As baby teeth fall and adult teeth begin to emerge it is essential to ensure the proper alignment is maintained.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Adolescent Dentistry<\/h5>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When permanent teeth erupt in the wrong way it can result in crooked, crowded and misaligned teeth. In some cases\u2019 baby teeth may fall too early. When this happens a dentist that specializes in infant dentistry may advise that space maintainers are the best option. Space maintainers are used to ensure that surrounding teeth do not shift and move when a baby tooth is missing. It is also essential to teach children how to brush and floss properly at an early age. Oral health education for children is one of the most important aspects of developing good habits that will carry well into adulthood.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"left\",\"id\":1179,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"alignleft size-large\"><img src=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/06\/pediatric-dentistry.jpg\" alt=\"Adolescent Dentistry\" class=\"wp-image-1179\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n<!-- \/wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Fluoride Treatment<\/h5>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even issues involving thumb sucking must be addressed by dental care providers that treat children. Fluoride treatment and the sealing of teeth are also routinely discussed with parents in terms of providing children with the best possible dental treatment going forward. As a note, a pediatric dentist will also have on hand instruments and equipment that is specially designed specifically for use with children\u2019s teeth. Even the dental chair will be smaller and more suitable for children. These and other reasons make it clear to see why it is important to choose the right dentist for your children. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/contact\/\">Contact<\/a> your dentists in Pinole, Azadeh Hosseini, DDS and Ghazal Hosseini, DDS at <a href=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/\">Top Pinole Dental<\/a> and  today for more information on adolescents pediatric dentistry.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":6} -->\n<h6>References:<br> [1] <a href=\"https:\/\/www.happykidsdental.org\/pediatric-dentistry-for-adolescents\/\">Pediatric Dentistry For Adolescents<\/a><br> [2] <a href=\"https:\/\/www.walnutcreekdental.net\/special-care-for-kids-teeth\/\">Special Care For Kids Teeth<\/a><\/h6>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->",
