        "title": "Restoration Options For Missing Teeth",
        "excerpt": "As with many other types of dental related issues, missing teeth can result in other complications over time if the situation is left untreated. That is why it is essential that those missing one or more teeth seek out the guidance and treatment of a dental care provider as soon as possible. Keep in mind [&hellip;]",
        "author": "Top Pinole Dental",
        "content": "<!-- wp:image {\"id\":553,\"align\":\"right\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"alignright\"><img src=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/07\/khgf7.jpg\" alt=\"Restoration Options For Missing Teeth\" class=\"wp-image-553\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n<!-- \/wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As with many other types of dental related issues, missing teeth can result in other complications over time if the situation is left untreated. That is why it is essential that those missing one or more teeth seek out the guidance and treatment of a dental care provider as soon as possible. Keep in mind that there are a number of options available as a way to restore functionality and dental attractiveness. Teeth are lost for many reasons today. This can include everything from decay to accident related injuries.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Pain Or Sensitivity<\/h5>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When a tooth is left untreated after it has become injured, it will eventually become loose and fall out. You should keep in mind that immediately following the loss of a tooth an individual will experience pain or sensitivity. Tooth loss can have a direct impact on everything from speech to eating and other similar types of activities. It is also important to note that once a tooth has been lost, other teeth will shift over time. This can result in teeth becoming crooked and less functional. Replacing a missing tooth is not as difficult as it may sound. As a matter of fact, dental implants are an excellent option as are implant supported dental bridges.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":552,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"alignleft\"><img src=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/07\/dental-implants20175.jpg\" alt=\"Patients Have Choices Today\" class=\"wp-image-552\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n<!-- \/wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Patients Have Choices Today<\/h5>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In most cases an oral surgeon will carefully place a metal post into the jawbone that in essence becomes an artificial tooth root. This results in long-term strength, stability and durability. Dental implant dentistry has become so advanced and so reliable that it produces outstanding results when it comes to replacing a missing tooth or multiple missing teeth. Other options include dentures and dental bridges. Whatever the case may be one thing is sure and that is that patients have choices today when they have missing teeth. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/contact\/\">Contact<\/a> your Pinole dentist, Dr. Azadeh Hosseini and Dr. Ghazal Hosseini at <a href=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/\">Top Pinole Dental<\/a> for more information on restoration options as they relate to missing teeth.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":6} -->\n<h6>References:<br> [1] <a href=\"https:\/\/dentalimplantsolutions.net\/missing-teeth-restoration-options\/\">Missing Teeth - Restoration Options<\/a><br> [2] <a href=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/2019\/03\/29\/learn-more-about-porcelain-bridges\/\">Learn More About Porcelain Bridges<\/a><br> [3] <a href=\"https:\/\/www.walnutcreekdental.net\/blog\/2019\/04\/03\/multiple-missing-teeth-and-dental-implant-options\/\">Multiple Missing Teeth and Dental Implant Options<\/a><\/h6>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->",
