        "title": "Gum Diseases and Their Side Effects On Overall Health",
        "excerpt": "There are a number of signs that gum disease may be present in an individual. For example, tooth sensitivity is a common indicator that some level of gum disease is present. In addition, everything from tooth loss to an abscessed tooth or even bad breath may be a sign that gum disease is an issue. [&hellip;]",
        "author": "Top Pinole Dental",
        "content": "<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"right\",\"id\":444} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"alignright\"><img src=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/04\/how-to-reverse-gingivitis.jpeg\" alt=\"Gum Diseases and Their Side Effects On Overall Health\" class=\"wp-image-444\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n<!-- \/wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are a number of signs that gum disease may be present in an individual. For example, tooth sensitivity is a common indicator that some level of gum disease is present. In addition, everything from tooth loss to an abscessed tooth or even bad breath may be a sign that gum disease is an issue. Also, when the gums become red or swollen or if there is bleeding there should be a concern for the possibility of gum disease. Always consult with your dental care provider if you have any of these signs or symptoms. Meanwhile, discussed below are some of the side effects of gum diseases on overall health.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Inflammation Associated With Gum Disease<\/h5>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The side effects of gum disease on human health can be rather substantial. For example, many studies shave suggested that gum disease could increase the risk of stroke and heart disease. One thought is that the inflammation associated with gum disease may cause a chronic inflammation response throughout the body, thus causing problems across multiple body systems. Diabetes is another concern that should be discussed when talking about gum disease. As a mater of fact, those with diabetes have a greater likelihood of having some degree of gum disease. <\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"left\",\"id\":443} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"alignleft\"><img src=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/04\/Gum-Copy.jpg\" alt=\"Chronic Kidney Disease is Equally a Concern\" class=\"wp-image-443\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n<!-- \/wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Chronic Kidney Disease is Equally a Concern<\/h5>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The connection between gum disease and diabetes is most probably due to high blood glucose. As a note, those with diabetes should take extra care to brush and floss often and do so in a very thorough way. Chronic kidney disease is equally a concern when it comes to gum disease. Research has indicated that those with serious gum tissue disease have a higher incidence of chronic kidney disease. If any of these conditions are a concern to you it is always best to talk with your general medical care provider and dental care provider as a way to preclude potentially serious health issues. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/contact\/\">Contact<\/a> your Pinole dentists, Dr. Azadeh Hosseini and Dr. Ghazal Hosseini at <a href=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/\">Top Pinole Dental<\/a> today to learn more about the side effects of gum diseases.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":6} -->\n<h6>References:<br> [1] <a href=\"https:\/\/www.walnutcreekdental.net\/blog\/2018\/07\/10\/gum-disease-signs-and-diagnosis\/\">Gum Disease - Signs and Diagnosis<\/a><br> [2] <a href=\"https:\/\/www.toppinoledental.com\/how-to-properly-brush-and-floss\/\">How To Properly Brush And Floss<\/a><\/h6>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->",
